HEADWORD: Blastopore
<hw>Blas"to*pore</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>blasto`s</grk> sprout + E. <ets>pore</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The pore or opening leading into the cavity of
invagination, or archenteron.</def> <note>[See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Invagination</er>.]</note> <rj><au>Balfour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

